The paper deals with image denoising using deep learning techniques, specifically a generative adversarial network (GAN) with Wasserstein distance and perceptual loss. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of GANs and deep learning techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of optimal transport theory, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with reducing radiation dose in medical imaging, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category.
